      id="bson_append_oid">
  <info>
    <link type="guide" xref="bson_t" group="function"/>
  </info>
  <title>bson_append_oid()</title>

  <section id="synopsis">
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <synopsis><code mime="text/x-csrc"><![CDATA[bool
bson_append_oid (bson_t           *bson,
                 const char       *key,
                 int               key_length,
                 const bson_oid_t *oid);
]]></code></synopsis>
  </section>

  <section id="parameters">
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
      <tr><td><p>bson</p></td><td><p>A <code xref="bson_t">bson_t</code>.</p></td></tr>
      <tr><td><p>key</p></td><td><p>An ASCII C string containing the name of the field.</p></td></tr>
      <tr><td><p>key_length</p></td><td><p>The length of <code>key</code> in bytes, or -1 to determine the length with <code>strlen()</code>.</p></td></tr>
      <tr><td><p>oid</p></td><td><p>A bson_oid_t.</p></td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="description">
    <title>Description</title>
    <p>The <code xref="bson_append_oid">bson_append_oid()</code> function shall append a new element to <code>bson</code> of type BSON_TYPE_OID. <code>oid</code> <em>MUST</em> be a pointer to a <code xref="bson_oid_t">bson_oid_t</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="return">
    <title>Returns</title>
    <p>true if the operation was applied successfully, otherwise false and <code>bson</code> should be discarded.</p>
  </section>
</page>
